        "username": "Battler",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/battler/{size}/208_2.png",
        "created_at": "2004-08-07T22:57:41.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Well I met a guy on the ICQ, who is from South Korea, from Gwangju (or how is it spelled), and who started to make a Korean translation for LBA 2 :eek:, but he didnt know, where to find suitable programs. I sent him my WinHQR and N-SoftInds LBA Text File Editor, and made him a font (which Im going to publicly release tomorrow). There was only one problem: that for complete Korean, LBA 2 would have to be Unicode or at least DBCS version, so the translation will be in Hangul Jamo.</p>\n<p>As evidence, I attached some screenshots, of what so far has been translated (3 in-game and 1 menu screenshots, tested on lbaguy3ds older version of LBA :-/). <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
